Sample collection.name: Sample collection
Sample collection.description: A procedure whereby biological samples for an experiment are sourced.

Mass spectrometry.name: Mass spectrometry
Mass spectrometry.description: Spectrometry where the sample is converted into gaseous ions which are characterised by their mass-to-charge ratio and relative abundance.

Scan polarity.definition: Ionization polarity is a device configuration of a ionization source whether the ions charge is negative or positive or alternating.

Ion source.definition: The method by which gas phase ions are generated from the sample

Mass analyzer.definition: Mass analyzer separates the ions according to their mass-to-charge ratio.

Data transformation.name: Data transformation
Data transformation.description: A planned process that produces output data from raw data.

Metabolite identification.name: Metabolite identification
Metabolite identification.description: Identification of the breakdown products of a substance, either through chemical instability or the actions of enzymes within the body.
